lines.text: there's a place off ocean avenue
where i used to sit and talk with you.
we were both sixteen and it felt so right,
sleeping all day, staying up all
on the corner at cherry street,
we would walk on the beach
we were both eighteen and it felt so right,
sleeping all day, staying up all
if i could find you now,
let your waves crash down on me
and take me away, yeah yeah
i dream and it gets me by
i can make believe that you're here
if i could find you now,
let your waves crash down on me
i remember the look in your eyes,
when i told you that this was goodbye.
you were begging me not tonight.
we're looking up at the same night sky.
we keep pretending the sun will not rise.
we'll be together for one more night,
if i could find you now,
let your waves crash down on me
and take me away, yeah yeah.
